dbackModal_main_2534555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zpq1665702960457.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpq1665702960457.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpq1665702960457.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zpq1665702960457\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Field Management on Oracle\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Mandatory fields are created with the Not Null constraint, unless they are part of the\n      primary key. This is because Primary Key fields in Oracle implicitly have the Not Null\n      constraint.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__section_wh1_wv4_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d118464e51\">Segmented Interfaces</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__p_d56507e1_d56508e1_d56509e1\">Uniface uses segmented I/O provided by Oracle when\n            reading a field with a segmented interface. The Oracle connector implements BLOBs as\n            CLOB and BLOB data types, which are also written to the database in segments.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__note_bwb_xv4_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> If you use segmented fields on a platform more\n            restrictive than a 32-bit virtual memory operating system, you can encounter severe\n            restrictions when attempting to update or insert a record. Furthermore, updating or\n            inserting large segmented fields can cause other activities on your system to fail. In\n            this case, consider using the Uniface proprietary variable-length techniques (overflow\n            tables) instead of the segmented field interface. To do so, set the <code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ptz1665702732397.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ptz1665702732397.html\" title=\"Disable BLOB support. Map fields with segmented interface into the variable portion of the record.\">disable segmented fields</a></code> connector option.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__p_d56510e1_d56511e1_d56512e1\">If the amount of memory required to write the\n            segmented field cannot be allocated, the following error can occur:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__pre_dwb_xv4_jcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Oracle connector Error[-4]: Dynamic memory allocation failed.</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpq1665702960457__p_d56513e1_d56514e1_d56515e1\">Increasing available memory can solve the problem. For\n            example, with virtual memory operating systems, you can increase storage available for\n            paging and swapping.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field Management on Oracle Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field Management on Oracle Mandatory fields are created with the Not Null constraint, unless they are part of the primary key. This is because Primary Key fields in Oracle implicitly have the Not Null constraint. Segmented Interfaces Uniface uses segmented I/O provided by Oracle when reading a field with a segmented interface. The Oracle connector implements BLOBs as CLOB and BLOB data types, which are also written to the database in segments. CAUTION: If you use segmented fields on a platform more restrictive than a 32-bit virtual memory operating system, you can encounter severe restrictions when attempting to update or insert a record. Furthermore, updating or inserting large segmented fields can cause other activities on your system to fail. In this case, consider using the Uniface proprietary variable-length techniques (overflow tables) instead of the segmented field interface. To do so, set the disable segmented fields connector option. If the amount of memory required to write the segmented field cannot be allocated, the following error can occur: Oracle connector Error[-4]: Dynamic memory allocation failed. Copy Increasing available memory can solve the problem. For example, with virtual memory operating systems, you can increase storage available for paging and swapping. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}